What you need to know:  The move reverses an order from Biden's predecessor Donald Trump, who in late 2020 pulled nearly all US forces from the Horn of African nation as he sought to wind down US military engagements abroad during his final weeks in office.By reinserting US troops, Washington will reduce the risks involved in back-and-forth mobilisations of forces that have been conducting counterterrorism operations inside Somalia.The move would boost efficiency and the effectiveness of special operators, and allow for uninterrupted training periods with local partners.